.IP \(bu
With a cold-ass lil correspondin per-destination recipient limit >
1, tha rate delay specifies tha time between deliveries ta the
\fIsame domain\fR.  Different domains is served up in parallel,
subject ta tha process limits specified up in master.cf.
.IP \(bu
With a cold-ass lil correspondin per-destination recipient limit equal
to 1, tha rate delay specifies tha time between deliveries ta the
\fIsame recipient\fR. Different recipients is served up in
parallel, subject ta tha process limits specified up in master.cf.
.br
.PP
To enable tha delay, specify a non-zero time value (an integral
value plus a optionizzle one-letta suffix dat specifies tha time
unit).
.PP
Time units: s (seconds), m (minutes), h (hours), d (days), w
(weeks). Da default time unit is s (seconds).
.PP
NOTE: tha delay is enforced by tha queue manager n' shit. Da delay
timer state do not survive "\fBpostfix reload\fR" or "\fBpostfix
stop\fR".
.PP
Use \fItransport\fR_destination_rate_delay ta specify a
transport-specific override, where \fItransport\fR is tha master.cf
name of tha message delivery transport.
.PP
NOTE: wit a non-zero _destination_rate_delay, specify a
\fItransport\fR_destination_concurrency_failed_cohort_limit of 10
