as bigs up:
.IP \(bu
It chizzlez tha meanin of tha correspondin per-destination
concurrency limit, from concurrency of deliveries ta tha \fIsame
domain\fR tha fuck into concurrency of deliveries ta tha \fIsame recipient\fR.
Different recipients is served up in parallel, subject ta the
process limits specified up in master.cf.
.IP \(bu
It chizzlez tha meanin of tha correspondin per-destination
rate delay, from tha delay between deliveries ta tha \fIsame
domain\fR tha fuck into tha delay between deliveries ta tha \fIsame
recipient\fR.  Again, different recipients is served up in parallel,
subject ta tha process limits specified up in master.cf.
.IP \(bu
It chizzlez tha meanin of other correspondin per-destination
settings up in a similar manner, from settings fo' delivery ta the
\fIsame domain\fR tha fuck into settings fo' delivery ta tha \fIsame
recipient\fR.
.br
.PP
Use \fItransport\fR_destination_recipient_limit ta specify a
transport-specific override, where \fItransport\fR is tha master.cf
name of tha message delivery transport.
.SH default_extra_recipient_limit (default: 1000)
Da default value fo' tha extra per-transhiznit limit imposed on the
