more of dem at least once every last muthafuckin dis nuff seconds.  This is used to
make shizzle tha recipients is refilled up in timely manner even when
$default_recipient_refill_limit is too high fo' too slow deliveries.
.PP
Use \fItransport\fR_recipient_refill_delay ta specify a
transport-specific override, where \fItransport\fR is tha master.cf
name of tha message delivery transport.
.PP
This feature be available up in Postfix 2.4 n' later.
.SH default_recipient_refill_limit (default: 100)
Da default per-transhiznit limit on tha number of recipients refilled at
