.SH postscreen_access_list (default: permit_mynetworks)
Permanent white/blacklist fo' remote SMTP client IP addresses.
\fBpostscreen\fR(8) searches dis list immediately afta a remote SMTP
client connects, n' you can put dat on yo' toast.  Specify a cold-ass lil comma- or whitespace-separated list of
commandz (in upper or lower case) or lookup tables. Da search stops
upon tha straight-up original gangsta command dat fires fo' tha client IP address.
.IP "\fB permit_mynetworks \fR"
