then tha Postfix SMTP client will not
attempt ta authenticate ta tha remote host.
.PP
Da Postfix SMTP client opens tha lookup table before goin to
chroot jail, so you can leave tha password file up in /etc/postfix.
.SH smtp_sasl_path (default: empty)
Implementation-specific shiznit dat tha Postfix SMTP client
passes all up in to
the SASL plug-in implementation dat is selected with
\fBsmtp_sasl_type\fR.  Typically dis specifies tha name of a
