.SH smtp_tls_mandatory_protocols (default: !SSLv2)
List of SSL/TLS protocols dat tha Postfix SMTP client will use with
mandatory TLS encryption. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch.  In main.cf tha joints is separated by
whitespace, commas or colons. In tha policy table "protocols" attribute
(see smtp_tls_policy_maps) tha only valid separator is colon. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch fo' realz. An
empty value means allow all protocols. Da valid protocol names, (see
\\fBfBSSL_get_version\fR(3)\fR), is "SSLv2", "SSLv3" n' "TLSv1".
.PP
Note: Az of OpenSSL 1.0.1 two freshly smoked up protocols is defined, "TLSv1.1"
and "TLSv1.2". If a olda Postfix version is linked against OpenSSL
1.0.1 or later, these, or any other freshly smoked up protocol versions, are
unconditionally enabled.
.PP
With Postfix >= 2.5 tha parameta syntax is expanded ta support
protocol exclusions. One can now explicitly exclude SSLv2 by setting
"smtp_tls_mandatory_protocols = !SSLv2". To exclude both SSLv2 and
SSLv3 set "smtp_tls_mandatory_protocols = !SSLv2, !SSLv3". Listing
the protocols ta include, rather than protocols ta exclude, is
supported yo, but not recommended. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Da exclusion form mo' closely
matches tha behavior when tha OpenSSL library is newer than Postfix.
.PP
Since SSL version 2 has known protocol weaknesses n' is now
deprecated, tha default settin excludes "SSLv2".  This means dat by
default, SSL version 2 aint gonna be used all up in tha "encrypt" securitizzle level
and higher.
.PP
See tha documentation of tha smtp_tls_policy_maps parameta and
TLS_README fo' mo' shiznit bout securitizzle levels.
.PP
Example:
.PP
.nf
.na
.ft C
# Preferred form wit Postfix >= 2.5:
smtp_tls_mandatory_protocols = !SSLv2, !SSLv3
# Alternatizzle form.
smtp_tls_mandatory_protocols = TLSv1
.fi
.ad
.ft R
.PP
This feature be available up in Postfix 2.3 n' later.
