Da default time unit is s (seconds).
.PP
This feature be available up in Postfix 2.1 n' later.
.SH smtpd_authorized_verp_clients (default: $authorized_verp_clients)
What remote SMTP clients is allowed ta specify tha XVERP command.
This command requests dat mail be served up one recipient at a
time wit a per recipient return address.
.PP
By default, no clients is allowed ta specify XVERP.
.PP
This parameta was renamed wit Postfix version 2.1. Da default value
is backwardz compatible wit Postfix version 2.0.
.PP
Specify a list of network/netmask patterns, separated by commas
and/or whitespace. Da mask specifies tha number of bits up in the
network part of a host address. Yo ass can also specify hostnames or
\&.domain names (the initial dot causes tha domain ta match any name
below it),  "/file/name" or "type:table" patterns.  A "/file/name"
pattern is replaced by its contents; a "type:table" lookup table
is matched when a table entry matches a lookup strang (the lookup
result is ignored).  Continue long lines by startin tha next line
with whitespace. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. Specify "!pattern" ta exclude a address or network
block from tha list. Da form "!/file/name" is supported only in
Postfix version 2.4 n' later.
.PP
Note: IP version 6 address shiznit must be specified inside
[] up in tha smtpd_authorized_verp_clients value, n' in
filez specified wit "/file/name".  IP version 6 addresses contain
