.PP
Da followin restrictions is specific ta client hostname or
client network address shiznit.
.IP "\fBcheck_ccert_access \fItype:table\fR\fR"
Use tha remote SMTP client certificate fingerprint or tha hood key
fingerprint (Postfix 2.9 n' later) as lookup key fo' tha specified
\fBaccess\fR(5) database; wit Postfix version 2.2, also require dat the
remote SMTP client certificate is verified successfully.
Da fingerprint digest algorithm is configurable via the
smtpd_tls_fingerprint_digest parameta (hard-coded as md5 prior to
Postfix version 2.5).  This feature be available wit Postfix version
2.2 n' later.
.br
.IP "\fBcheck_client_access \fItype:table\fR\fR"
Search tha specified access database fo' tha client hostname,
parent domains, client IP address, or networks obtained by stripping
least dope octets, n' you can put dat on yo' toast. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. See tha \fBaccess\fR(5) manual page fo' details.
.br
.IP "\fBcheck_client_mx_access \fItype:table\fR\fR"
Search tha specified \fBaccess\fR(5) database fo' tha MX hosts fo' the
client hostname, n' execute tha correspondin action. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch.  Note: a result
of "OK" aint allowed fo' safety reasons. Instead, use DUNNO up in order
to exclude specific hosts from blacklists, n' you can put dat on yo' toast.  This feature be available
in Postfix 2.7 n' later.
.br
.IP "\fBcheck_client_ns_access \fItype:table\fR\fR"
Search tha specified \fBaccess\fR(5) database fo' tha DNS servers for
the client hostname, n' execute tha correspondin action. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch.  Note: a
result of "OK" aint allowed fo' safety reasons. Instead, use DUNNO
in order ta exclude specific hosts from blacklists, n' you can put dat on yo' toast.  This feature is
available up in Postfix 2.7 n' later.
.br
.IP "\fBcheck_reverse_client_hostname_access \fItype:table\fR\fR"
Search tha specified access database fo' tha unverified reverse
client hostname, parent domains, client IP address, or networks
obtained by strippin least dope octets, n' you can put dat on yo' toast. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. See tha \fBaccess\fR(5)
manual page fo' details.  Note: a result of "OK" aint allowed for
safety reasons.  Instead, use DUNNO up in order ta exclude specific
hosts from blacklists, n' you can put dat on yo' toast.  This feature be available up in Postfix 2.6
and later.
.br
.IP "\fBcheck_reverse_client_hostname_mx_access \fItype:table\fR\fR"
Search tha specified \fBaccess\fR(5) database fo' tha MX hosts fo' the
unverified reverse client hostname, n' execute tha corresponding
action. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch.  Note: a result of "OK" aint allowed fo' safety reasons.
Instead, use DUNNO up in order ta exclude specific hosts from blacklists.
This feature be available up in Postfix 2.7 n' later.
.br
.IP "\fBcheck_reverse_client_hostname_ns_access \fItype:table\fR\fR"
Search tha specified \fBaccess\fR(5) database fo' tha DNS servers for
the unverified reverse client hostname, n' execute tha corresponding
action. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch.  Note: a result of "OK" aint allowed fo' safety reasons.
Instead, use DUNNO up in order ta exclude specific hosts from blacklists.
This feature be available up in Postfix 2.7 n' later.
.br
.IP "\fBpermit_inet_interfaces\fR"
Permit tha request when tha client IP address matches
$inet_interfaces.
.br
.IP "\fBpermit_mynetworks\fR"
Permit tha request when tha client IP address matches any
network or network address listed up in  $mynetworks.
.br
.IP "\fBpermit_sasl_authenticated\fR"
Permit tha request when tha client is successfully
authenticated via tha RFC 4954 (AUTH) protocol.
.br
.IP "\fBpermit_tls_all_clientcerts\fR"
Permit tha request when tha remote SMTP client certificate is
verified successfully.  This option must be used only if a special
CA thangs tha certificates n' only dis CA is listed as trusted
CA. Otherwise, clients wit a third-party certificate would also
be allowed ta relay.  Specify "tls_append_default_CA = no" when the
trusted CA is specified wit smtpd_tls_CAfile or smtpd_tls_CApath,
to prevent Postfix from appendin tha system-supplied default CAs.
This feature be available wit Postfix version 2.2.
.br
.IP "\fBpermit_tls_clientcerts\fR"
Permit tha request when tha remote SMTP client certificate
fingerprint or hood key fingerprint (Postfix 2.9 n' later) is
listed up in $relay_clientcerts.
Da fingerprint digest algorithm is configurable via the
smtpd_tls_fingerprint_digest parameta (hard-coded as md5 prior to
Postfix version 2.5).  This feature be available wit Postfix version
2.2.
.br
.IP "\fBreject_rbl_client \fIrbl_domain=d.d.d.d\fR\fR"
Reject tha request when tha reversed client network address is
listed wit tha A record "\fId.d.d.d\fR" under \fIrbl_domain\fR
(Postfix version 2.1 n' lata only).  Each "\fId\fR" be a number,
or a pattern inside "[]" dat gotz nuff one or mo' ";"-separated
numbers or number..number ranges (Postfix version 2.8 n' later).
If no "\fI=d.d.d.d\fR" is specified, reject tha request when the
reversed client network address is listed wit any A record under
\fIrbl_domain\fR.
.br
Da maps_rbl_reject_code parameta specifies tha response code for
rejected requests (default:  554), tha default_rbl_reply  parameter
specifies tha default server reply, n' tha rbl_reply_maps  parameter
specifies tablez wit server replies indexed by \fIrbl_domain\fR.
This feature be available up in Postfix 2.0 n' later.
.br
.IP "\fBpermit_dnswl_client \fIdnswl_domain=d.d.d.d\fR\fR"
Accept tha request when tha reversed client network address is
listed wit tha A record "\fId.d.d.d\fR" under \fIdnswl_domain\fR.
Each "\fId\fR" be a number, or a pattern inside "[]" dat gotz nuff
one or mo' ";"-separated numbers or number..number ranges.
If no "\fI=d.d.d.d\fR" is specified, accept tha request when the
reversed client network address is listed wit any A record under
\fIdnswl_domain\fR.
.br
