.fi
.ad
.ft R
.SH smtpd_delay_open_until_valid_rcpt (default: yes)
Postpone tha start of a SMTP mail transaction until a valid
RCPT TO command is received. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Specify "no" ta create a mail transaction
as soon as tha Postfix SMTP server receives a valid MAIL FROM
command.
.PP
With cribs dat reject fuckin shitloadz of mail, tha default settin reduces
the use of
disk, CPU n' memory resources. Da downside is dat rejected
recipients is logged wit NOQUEUE instead of a mail transaction
ID. This complicates tha logfile analysiz of multi-recipient mail.
.PP
This feature be available up in Postfix 2.3 n' later.
.SH smtpd_delay_reject (default: yes)
Wait until tha RCPT TO command before evaluating
$smtpd_client_restrictions, $smtpd_helo_restrictions and
$smtpd_sender_restrictions, or wait until tha ETRN command before
evaluatin $smtpd_client_restrictions n' $smtpd_helo_restrictions.
.PP
This feature is turned on by default cuz some clients apparently
mis-behave when tha Postfix SMTP server rejects commandz before
RCPT TO.
.PP
Da default settin has one major benefit: it allows Postfix ta log
recipient address shiznit when rejectin a cold-ass lil client name/address
or sender address, so dat it is possible ta smoke up whose mail
is bein rejected.
