This feature be available up in Postfix 2.2 n' later.
.PP
See smtpd_data_restrictions fo' details n' limitations.
.SH smtpd_enforce_tls (default: no)
Mandatory TLS: announce STARTTLS support ta remote SMTP clients,
and require dat clients use TLS encryption. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch.  Accordin ta RFC 2487
this MUST NOT be applied up in case of a publicly-referenced SMTP
server n' shit.  This option is therefore off by default.
.PP
Note 1: "smtpd_enforce_tls = yes" implies "smtpd_tls_auth_only = yes".
.PP
Note 2: when invoked via "\fBsendmail -bs\fR", Postfix aint NEVER gonna offer
STARTTLS cuz of insufficient privileges ta access tha server private
key. This is intended behavior.
.PP
This feature be available up in Postfix 2.2 n' later n' shit. With
Postfix 2.3 n' lata use smtpd_tls_security_level instead.
.SH smtpd_error_sleep_time (default: 1s)
With Postfix version 2.1 n' later: tha SMTP server response delay after
a client has made mo' than $smtpd_soft_error_limit errors, and
fewer than $smtpd_hard_error_limit errors, without deliverin mail.
.PP
With Postfix version 2.0 n' earlier: tha SMTP server delay before
sendin a reject (4xx or 5xx) response, when tha client has made
fewer than $smtpd_soft_error_limit errors without delivering
mail.
.SH smtpd_etrn_restrictions (default: empty)
Optionizzle restrictions dat tha Postfix SMTP server applies up in the
context of a cold-ass lil client ETRN command.
See SMTPD_ACCESS_README, section "Delayed evaluation of SMTP access
restriction lists" fo' a gangbangin' finger-lickin' rap of evaluation context n' time.
