.PP
Da followin restrictions is specific ta tha recipient address
that is received wit tha RCPT TO command.
.IP "\fBcheck_recipient_access \fItype:table\fR\fR"
Search tha specified \fBaccess\fR(5) database fo' tha resolved RCPT
TO address, domain, parent domains, or localpart@, n' execute the
correspondin action.
.br
.IP "\fBcheck_recipient_mx_access \fItype:table\fR\fR"
Search tha specified \fBaccess\fR(5) database fo' tha MX hosts for
the RCPT TO domain, n' execute tha correspondin action. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch.  Note:
a result of "OK" aint allowed fo' safety reasons. Instead, use
DUNNO up in order ta exclude specific hosts from blacklists, n' you can put dat on yo' toast.  This
feature be available up in Postfix 2.1 n' later.
.br
.IP "\fBcheck_recipient_ns_access \fItype:table\fR\fR"
Search tha specified \fBaccess\fR(5) database fo' tha DNS servers
for tha RCPT TO domain, n' execute tha correspondin action.
Note: a result of "OK" aint allowed fo' safety reasons. Instead,
use DUNNO up in order ta exclude specific hosts from blacklists, n' you can put dat on yo' toast.  This
feature be available up in Postfix 2.1 n' later.
.br
.IP "\fBpermit_auth_destination\fR"
Permit tha request when one of tha followin is true:
.IP \(bu
Postfix is mail forwarder: tha resolved RCPT TO domain matches
$relay_domains or a subdomain thereof, n' tha address gotz nuff no
sender-specified routin (user@elsewhere@domain),
.IP \(bu
Postfix is tha final destination: tha resolved RCPT TO domain
matches $mydestination, $inet_interfaces, $proxy_interfaces,
$virtual_alias_domains, or $virtual_mailbox_domains, n' tha address
gotz nuff no sender-specified routin (user@elsewhere@domain).
.br
.br
.IP "\fBpermit_mx_backup\fR"
Permit tha request when tha local mail system is backup MX for
the RCPT TO domain, or when tha domain be a authorized destination
(see permit_auth_destination fo' definition).
.IP \(bu
Safety: permit_mx_backup do not accept addresses dat have
sender-specified routin shiznit (example: user@elsewhere@domain).
.IP \(bu
Safety: permit_mx_backup can be vulnerable ta mis-use when
access aint restricted wit permit_mx_backup_networks.
.IP \(bu
Safety: az of Postfix version 2.3, permit_mx_backup no longer
accepts tha address when tha local mail system is primary MX for
the recipient domain. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch.  Exception: permit_mx_backup accepts tha address
when it specifies a authorized destination (see permit_auth_destination
for definition).
.IP \(bu
Limitation: mail may be rejected up in case of a temporary DNS
lookup problem wit Postfix prior ta version 2.0.
.br
.br
.IP "\fBreject_non_fqdn_recipient\fR"
Reject tha request when tha RCPT TO address aint in
fully-qualified domain form, as required by tha RFC.
.br
The
non_fqdn_reject_code parameta specifies tha response code for
rejected requests (default: 504).
.br
.IP "\fBreject_rhsbl_recipient \fIrbl_domain=d.d.d.d\fR\fR"
