A record "\fId.d.d.d\fR" under \fIrbl_domain\fR (Postfix version
2.1 n' lata only).  Each "\fId\fR" be a number, or a pattern
inside "[]" dat gotz nuff one or mo' ";"-separated numbers or
number..number ranges (Postfix version 2.8 n' later). If no
"\fI=d.d.d.d\fR" is specified, reject
the request when tha RCPT TO domain is listed with
any A record under \fIrbl_domain\fR.
.br
Da maps_rbl_reject_code
parameta specifies tha response code fo' rejected requests (default:
554); tha default_rbl_reply parameta specifies tha default server
reply; n' tha rbl_reply_maps parameta specifies tablez wit server
replies indexed by \fIrbl_domain\fR.  This feature be available
in Postfix version 2.0 n' later.
.br
.IP "\fBreject_unauth_destination\fR"
Reject tha request unless one of tha followin is true:
.IP \(bu
Postfix is mail forwarder: tha resolved RCPT TO domain matches
$relay_domains or a subdomain thereof, n' gotz nuff no sender-specified
routin (user@elsewhere@domain),
.IP \(bu
Postfix is tha final destination: tha resolved RCPT TO domain
matches $mydestination, $inet_interfaces, $proxy_interfaces,
$virtual_alias_domains, or $virtual_mailbox_domains, n' gotz nuff
no sender-specified routin (user@elsewhere@domain).
.br
Da relay_domains_reject_code parameta specifies tha response
code fo' rejected requests (default: 554).
.br
.IP "\fBdefer_unauth_destination\fR"
Reject tha same requests as reject_unauth_destination, wit a
non-permanent error code.  This feature be available up in Postfix
2.10 n' later.
.br
.IP "\fBreject_unknown_recipient_domain\fR"
Reject tha request when Postfix aint final destination for
the recipient domain, n' tha RCPT TO domain has 1) no DNS A or MX
record or 2) a malformed MX record like fuckin a record with
a zero-length MX hostname (Postfix version 2.3 n' later).
.br
The
unknown_address_reject_code parameta specifies tha numerical
response code fo' rejected requests (default: 450).  Da response
is always 450 up in case of a temporary DNS error.
.br
The
unknown_address_tempfail_action parameta specifies tha action
afta a temporary DNS error (default: defer_if_permit).
.br
.IP "\fBreject_unlisted_recipient\fR (with Postfix version 2.0: check_recipient_maps)"
Reject tha request when tha RCPT TO address aint listed in
the list of valid recipients fo' its domain class. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. See the
smtpd_reject_unlisted_recipient parameta description fo' details.
This feature be available up in Postfix 2.1 n' later.
.br
.IP "\fBreject_unverified_recipient\fR"
Reject tha request when mail ta tha RCPT TO address is known
to bounce, or when tha recipient address destination aint reachable.
Address verification shiznit is managed by tha \fBverify\fR(8) server;
see tha ADDRESS_VERIFICATION_README file fo' details.
.br
The
unverified_recipient_reject_code parameta specifies tha numerical
response code when a address is known ta bounce (default: 450,
change tha fuck into 550 when yo ass is Kool & Tha Gang dat it is safe ta do so).
.br
Da unverified_recipient_defer_code parameta specifies the
numerical response code when a address probe failed cuz of a
temporary problem (default: 450).
.br
The
unverified_recipient_tempfail_action parameta specifies tha action
afta addres probe failure cuz of a temporary problem (default:
defer_if_permit).
.br
This feature be available up in Postfix 2.1
and later.
.br
.br
.PP
Other restrictions dat is valid up in dis context:
.IP \(bu
Generic restrictions dat can be used
in any SMTP command context, busted lyrics bout under smtpd_client_restrictions.
.IP \(bu
SMTP command specific restrictions busted lyrics bout under
smtpd_client_restrictions, smtpd_helo_restrictions and
smtpd_sender_restrictions.
