Da SASL authentication securitizzle options dat tha Postfix SMTP
server uses fo' TLS encrypted SMTP sessions.
.PP
This feature be available up in Postfix 2.2 n' later.
.SH smtpd_sasl_type (default: cyrus)
Da SASL plug-in type dat tha Postfix SMTP server should use
for authentication. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. Da available types is listed wit the
"\fBpostconf -a\fR" command.
.PP
This feature be available up in Postfix 2.3 n' later.
.SH smtpd_sender_login_maps (default: empty)
Optionizzle lookup table wit tha SASL login names dat own sender
(MAIL FROM) addresses.
.PP
Specify zero or mo' "type:table" lookup tables. With lookups from
indexed filez like fuckin DB or DBM, or from networked tablez such as
NIS, LDAP or SQL, tha followin search operations is done wit a
sender address of \fIuser@domain\fR:
.IP "1) \fIuser@domain\fR"
This table lookup be always done n' has tha highest precedence.
.br
.IP "2) \fIuser\fR"
This table lookup is done only when tha \fIdomain\fR part of the
sender address matches $myorigin, $mydestination, $inet_interfaces
or $proxy_interfaces.
.br
.IP "3) \fI@domain\fR"
