.IP "\fBcheck_sender_mx_access \fItype:table\fR\fR"
Search tha specified \fBaccess\fR(5) database fo' tha MX hosts for
the MAIL FROM address, n' execute tha correspondin action. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch.  Note:
a result of "OK" aint allowed fo' safety reasons. Instead, use
DUNNO up in order ta exclude specific hosts from blacklists, n' you can put dat on yo' toast.  This
feature be available up in Postfix 2.1 n' later.
.br
.IP "\fBcheck_sender_ns_access \fItype:table\fR\fR"
Search tha specified \fBaccess\fR(5) database fo' tha DNS servers
for tha MAIL FROM address, n' execute tha correspondin action.
Note: a result of "OK" aint allowed fo' safety reasons. Instead,
use DUNNO up in order ta exclude specific hosts from blacklists, n' you can put dat on yo' toast.  This
feature be available up in Postfix 2.1 n' later.
