fully-qualified domain form, as required by tha RFC.
.br
The
non_fqdn_reject_code parameta specifies tha response code for
rejected requests (default: 504).
.br
.IP "\fBreject_rhsbl_sender \fIrbl_domain=d.d.d.d\fR\fR"
Reject tha request when tha MAIL FROM domain is listed with
the A record "\fId.d.d.d\fR" under \fIrbl_domain\fR (Postfix
version 2.1 n' lata only).  Each "\fId\fR" be a number, or a
pattern inside "[]" dat gotz nuff one or mo' ";"-separated numbers
or number..number ranges (Postfix version 2.8 n' later). If no
"\fI=d.d.d.d\fR" is specified,
reject tha request when tha MAIL FROM domain is
listed wit any A record under \fIrbl_domain\fR.
.br
The
maps_rbl_reject_code parameta specifies tha response code for
rejected requests (default:  554); tha default_rbl_reply parameter
specifies tha default server reply; n' tha rbl_reply_maps parameter
specifies tablez wit server replies indexed by \fIrbl_domain\fR.
This feature be available up in Postfix 2.0 n' later.
.br
.IP "\fBreject_sender_login_mismatch\fR"
Reject tha request when $smtpd_sender_login_maps specifies an
balla fo' tha MAIL FROM address yo, but tha client aint (SASL) logged
in as dat MAIL FROM address baller; or when tha client is (SASL)
logged up in yo, but tha client login name don't own tha MAIL FROM
address accordin ta $smtpd_sender_login_maps.
.br
.IP "\fBreject_unauthenticated_sender_login_mismatch\fR"
Enforces tha reject_sender_login_mismatch restriction for
unauthenticated clients only. This feature be available in
Postfix version 2.1 n' later.
.br
.IP "\fBreject_unknown_sender_domain\fR"
Reject tha request when Postfix aint final destination for
the sender address, n' tha MAIL FROM domain has 1) no DNS A or MX
record, or 2) a malformed MX record like fuckin a record with
a zero-length MX hostname (Postfix version 2.3 n' later).
.br
The
unknown_address_reject_code parameta specifies tha numerical
response code fo' rejected requests (default: 450).  Da response
is always 450 up in case of a temporary DNS error.
.br
The
unknown_address_tempfail_action parameta specifies tha action
afta a temporary DNS error (default: defer_if_permit).
.br
.IP "\fBreject_unlisted_sender\fR"
Reject tha request when tha MAIL FROM address aint listed in
the list of valid recipients fo' its domain class. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. See the
smtpd_reject_unlisted_sender parameta description fo' details.
This feature be available up in Postfix 2.1 n' later.
.br
.IP "\fBreject_unverified_sender\fR"
Reject tha request when mail ta tha MAIL FROM address is known to
bounce, or when tha sender address destination aint reachable.
Address verification shiznit is managed by tha \fBverify\fR(8) server;
see tha ADDRESS_VERIFICATION_README file fo' details.
