.SH smtpd_tls_exclude_ciphers (default: empty)
List of ciphers or cipher types ta exclude from tha SMTP server
cipher list at all TLS securitizzle levels. Excludin valid ciphers
can create interoperabilitizzle problems. DO NOT exclude ciphers unless it
is essential ta do so. This aint a OpenSSL cipherlist; it aint nuthin but a simple
list separated by whitespace and/or commas. Da elements is a single
cipher, or one or mo' "+" separated cipher properties, up in which case
only ciphers matchin \fBall\fR tha propertizzles is excluded.
.PP
Examplez (some of these will cause problems):
.sp
.in +4
.nf
.na
.ft C
smtpd_tls_exclude_ciphers = aNULL
smtpd_tls_exclude_ciphers = MD5, DES
