.SH smtpd_tls_mandatory_ciphers (default: medium)
Da minimum TLS cipher grade dat tha Postfix SMTP server will
use wit mandatory TLS encryption. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. Da default grade ("medium") is
sufficiently phat dat any benefit from globally restrictin TLS
sessions ta a mo' stringent grade is likely negligible, especially
given tha fact dat nuff implementations still do not offer any stronger
("high" grade) ciphers, while dem dat do, will always use "high"
grade ciphers. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. So insistin on "high" grade ciphers is generally
counter-productizzle fo' realz. Allowin "export" or "low" ciphers is typically
not a phat idea, as systems limited ta just these is limited to
obsolete browsers. No known SMTP clients fail ta support at least
one "medium" or "high" grade cipher.
